Title: [ANN][JPT] JPcompany -Jointly- MORE BONUS IN THE ICO WITH COMMON INVESTMENT
Body: The common wallet and the smart contract are keptin a hardware wallet offline (cold storage). If you are interested in how ICO projects will get on the Jpintly platform, then the mechanism is the following. I quote here, as it is described in our white paper https://docs.wixstatic.com/ugd/e2f41c_77b17e8747b347c4953fbd7de3401311.pdf  "Not all ICOs are created equal. ICOs must pass a rigorous process in order to be considered and selected by JP. First, the ICO must have a strong team, with verifiable experience. Next, they must have a strong concept as well as a working prototype or product. The JP Team will also research the top ICO listing and rating sites such as Cryptobriefing.com and ICOBench.com among others. In addition, the JP team will analyze and review activity on their social networks and on discord or telegram groups. The Jointly team will request a KYC certification in order to verify its identity".  Users will also be able to make proposals for adding the ICO projects, but it will be later. Do you have more question?

Author: JPcompany
Title: [ANN][JPT] JPcompany -Jointly- MORE BONUS IN THE ICO WITH COMMON INVESTMENT
Body: Do not be afraid for your means - Jointly is the decentralized platform and managed by a smart contract, fixing all the transactions that occur in the system. Smart contract will manage in a completely autonomous way the part of investment in the ICOs and the consequent subdivision and transmission of the token issued, with the bonuses, directly to the investor wallet. If you want to know the full procedure, we described it on the site:  The user from the main screen of JOINTLY will choose the ICO in which he will invest, then press on the "Invest" button. He will be shown the address of the common wallet and at this point the user of his wallet will send the ETH figure he wants to invest. Once the timer has expired or the maximum threshold of the common wallet will be reached, the smart contract will send the sum on the common wallet to the ICO which will issue the tokens with the relative bonuses. the user will be credited to the portfolio from which he has invested, the amount of tokens due.

Author: JPcompany

There is also the SendBackTokens feature that sends tokens back to investors basing facts on their initial investments, the reset function that automatically resets the users' investments and finally the setupNewICO that comes up with the new parameters of new ICO contracts.

Author: JPcompany
Title: [ANN][JPT] JPcompany -Jointly- MORE BONUS IN THE ICO WITH COMMON INVESTMENT

Based on the initial investment, the smart contract then redistributes the percentages of tokens with relative bonuses to the users.

Title: [ANN][JPT] JPcompany -Jointly- MORE BONUS IN THE ICO WITH COMMON INVESTMENT
Body: To answer this question, I will give an example  Generally a small-medium investor invests from 0.1 ETH to 3 ETH, and we want to take KickIco as a first example: investing 2 ETH the investor would have received 0.5% bonus (2 ETH = 6000 Kick = $ 474), which at the present value, including the bonus, would be 6030 Kick = $ 476. By investing the usual amount (2 ETH) using Jointly, the investor would have obtained 10% bonus, with a threshold of the common wallet at 1000 ETH, which today would have a value of $ 521. In conclusion, with the same amount invested you would have earned + $ 45!  You decide to buy coins yourself or use our platform and get the bonuses!

Author: JPcompany
Title: [ANN][JPT] JPcompany -Jointly- MORE BONUS IN THE ICO WITH COMMON INVESTMENT
Body: NEW UPDATE  Hello guys, these have been weeks full of work and we want to update you.  A new advisor has been added to the project, Do Yeop Kim, which with his knowledge will make a valuable contribution to the success of Jointly. Kim is an advisor for important ICOs like ICOmax, Blocknubie, Amicorum.LIVE and others  We have updated the site and the Whitepaper (available in a few days) with a new section "financial sector", where we illustrate the performance of the ICO market from 2014 to 2018. We have also added two graphs to show our forecasts on the volume trend of the Jointly platform over the years as well as Jointly's capitalization (with a consequent increase in the JPT token value).  One month is missing to the pre-ICO and in these weeks we have talked to many investors interested in supporting our marketing campaign  Finally we are proceeding with the development of the platform, precisely we are improving the functionality of the smart-contract at the base of the project. In agreement with the advisors we decided to decrease the bonus issued during the pre-ICO, precisely from 60% to 40%. Consequently the hard-cap will be higher, from 960,000€ to 1,440,000€. We have also decided to change the platform fee from 3.5% to 5% in order to have more funds to improve, in the future, the platform. We will keep you updated on the next steps, thanks everyone and stay tuned  www.jpcompany.solutions

Author: JPcompany
Title: [ANN][JPT] JPcompany -Jointly- MORE BONUS IN THE ICO WITH COMMON INVESTMENT
Body: Today we inaugurate a weekly column in which we will examine, every fryday, successful ICOs that have been realized, in order to show the potential of Jointly if it had been operational.  Generally a small-medium investor invests from 0.1 ETH to 3 ETH, and we want to take KickIco as a first example: investing 2 ETH the investor would have received 0.5% bonus (2 ETH = 6000 Kick = $ 474), which at the present value, including the bonus, would be 6030 Kick = $ 476.  By investing the usual amount (2 ETH) using Jointly, the investor would have obtained 10% bonus, with a threshold of the common wallet at 1000 ETH, which today would have a value of $ 521. In conclusion, with the same amount invested you would have earned + $ 45!  STAY TUNED
